results.name: A Zumkeller-type sequence (cf. A098550): a(n) = n if n <= 3, otherwise the smallest number not occurring earlier having at least one common factor with a(n-2)+a(n-1), but none with a(n-1).
comment: Conjectured to be a permutation of the positive integers.
See also A255972 for this conjecture. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Mar 12 2015
link: Peter J. C. Moses, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..5000

David L. Applegate, Hans Havermann, Bob Selcoe, Vladimir Shevelev, N. J. A. Sloane, and Reinhard Zumkeller, The Yellowstone Permutation, arXiv preprint arXiv:1501.01669 [math.NT], 2015 and J. Int. Seq. 18 (2015) 15.6.7.
mathematica: a[n_] := a[n] = If[n <= 3, n, For[k = 1, True, k++, If[FreeQ[Array[a, n-1], k], If[!CoprimeQ[k, a[n-2]+a[n-1]] && CoprimeQ[k, a[n-1]], Return[k]]]]];
program: f u v ws = g ws where
g (x:xs) = if gcd x (u + v) > 1 && gcd x v == 1
then x : f v x (delete x ws) else g xs
